==English==

===Noun===
'''Unaided Awareness'''  

# (Advertising) the percent of respondents who, without prompting, name a specific brand or product first when asked to list all the advertising they recall seeing in a general product category over the past 30 days, in advertising research.
#:''Since the company was new and had only started advertising two weeks before the research began, it was not surprising to see low '''unaided awareness''' of the brand.''

